---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import FeatureBlock from '../components/FeatureBlock.astro';
---

<Layout title="Insight Scout: Scenario Planning Tool for Startups | What-If Financial Modeling">
  <head>
    <meta name="description" content="Insight Scout is a scenario planning tool for startups offering what-if financial modeling, runway simulations, and AI-driven forecasts." />
    <meta name="keywords" content="scenario planning tool startups, what if financial modeling, startup cash flow scenario software" />
  </head>

  <Hero />
  <section class="container">
    <p style="font-size:2.2rem; margin:60px 0 32px;">Insight Scout is the leading scenario planning tool for startups, enabling precise what-if financial modeling.</p>
    <p style="font-size:2.2rem; margin:60px 0 32px;">Insight Scout offers advanced what-if financial scenario planning, integrated seamlessly with Insight Hunter's FP&A ecosystem.</p>
    <p>This tool enables side-by-side comparisons of best, base, and worst-case outcomes, modeling impacts on revenue, burn, hiring, and cash flow. AI refines predictions using historical data and real-time inputs from connected apps.</p>
    <p>Expanded features include driver-based simulations, seasonality adjustments, and unit economics breakdowns by segment. Share scenarios securely with advisors or investors via exportable reports. Scout supports multi-entity views in higher tiers for consolidated planning.</p>
    <img src="/images/scout-mockup.png" alt="Scout multi-scenario view" class="feature-image">
    <p>Essential for weekly strategic decisions in dynamic environments. Available standalone or enhanced in Standard/Full editions.</p>
    <a href="/shop" class="cta" style="display:inline-block; margin:60px auto;">Open Scout</a>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <FeatureBlock title="Dynamic Modeling" text="Real-time adjustments and AI accuracy for reliable what-if analysis across variables." image="/images/ai-query-mockup.png" alt="Scenario modeling" />
  </section>
</Layout>


